**Comprehensive Summary of Solicitation FA940126Q0002**

---

### **Solicitation Overview**
- **Title:** Aircrew Facility Linens
- **Solicitation Number:** FA940126Q0002
- **Organization:** DEPARTMENT OF THE AIR FORCE, 377TH AIR BASE WING (AFGSC), 377 MSG/CONTRACTING DIVISION – KIRTLAND AFB, NEW MEXICO
- **Location of Performance:** Kirtland Air Force Base (KAFB), Building 917, Albuquerque, NM 87117-0001

---

### **Key Dates**
- **Solicitation Posting Date:** 7 November 2025
- **Question Deadline:** 30 October 2025, 5:00 PM (MDT/MST)
- **Quote Submission Deadline:** 14 November 2025, 4:00 PM (MDT/MST)
- **Quote Validity:** 90 days from submission
- **Period of Performance:** 
  - Base Year: 1 December 2025 – 30 November 2026
  - Option Years I-IV through 30 November 2030 (each 12 months, see CLINs)

---

### **Submission Requirements**
- **Quotes must be submitted via email** to both the Contract Specialist and Contracting Officer identified below.
- **Electronic formats accepted:** .pdf, .doc, or .xls; Under 30MB (no .zip files or other formats).
- **Quote format:** Clear, concise, strictly adhering to requirements in the solicitation and Statement of Work (PWS); Maximum 5-6-page technical plan.
- **Do not include extraneous info:** Such as advertisements or marketing information.
- **Requirements for acceptance:** Technical plan must demonstrate capability and understanding of the PWS requirements; Pricing must be fair and reasonable.
- **Exceptions:** Any exceptions to solicitation terms must be clearly identified and justified.

---

### **Description of Work**
- **Scope:** The contractor shall provide all management, supervision, personnel, equipment, tools, supplies, transportation, materials, and other items needed to ensure laundry and dry cleaning services are provided for aircrew facility linens at KAFB, Building 917.
- **Performance Standards:** Workmanship and sanitation must conform with industry standards for cleanliness and appearance, and all applicable federal, state, local, and professional standards.
- **Periodicity:** Monthly invoices verified by Contracting Officer Representative (COR); service up to 40,000 pounds per year.
- **Essential Services:** Designated as mission-essential; contractor may be required to perform during crisis conditions per DoD regulations.

---

### **Insurance Requirements**
- While specific insurance requirements are not detailed in the provided context, contractors must adhere to federal, state, and local occupational safety standards. General guidance is to maintain all necessary insurances (workers’ comp, general liability, vehicle, etc.) appropriate for work on government installations. Reference to insurance requirements may also be found in the SF1449 and Attachment 1 (PWS).

